===Etymology===
1784,<ref name="oetyld"/> borrowed from {{bor|en|hi|अवतार}} or from {{bor|en|ur|اوتار|tr=avtār}}, both borrowed from {{der|en|sa|अवतार|t=descent of a deity from a heaven}}, a compound of {{m|sa|अव|t=off, away, down}} and the [[vṛddhi]]-stem of the root {{m|sa|तरति|√तॄ|t=to cross}}.

In computing use, saw some use in 1980s videos games – 1985 online role-playing game ''[[w:Habitat (video game)|Habitat]]'' by Lucasfilm Games (today {{w|LucasArts}}), by {{w|Chip Morningstar}} and {{w|Randy Farmer}},<ref name="Morabito">Morabito, Margaret. "Enter the Online World of LucasFilm." Run Aug. 1986: 24-28</ref> later versions of the ''[[w:Ultima (video game series)|Ultima]]'' series (following religious use in 1985 ''{{w|Ultima IV: Quest of the Avatar}}''), and 1989 {{w|pen and paper}} role-playing game ''{{w|Shadowrun}}.'' Popularized by 1992 novel ''{{w|Snow Crash}}'' by {{w|Neal Stephenson}}.<ref name="oetyld">{{R:Online Etymology Dictionary}}</ref>

